snippet.textDisplay: Its sad it happened and i can't understand why Kobe chose to fly when the FAA had issued a warning to all aircraft about the fog,low visibility and low ceiling. He was an experienced pilot,he knew the areas and he knows about certain areas are prone to fog and micro weather areas are rampant in such vast areas of California where you have mountains and canyons and moisture from the ocean in the cooler morning air. Taking 8 people into those conditions was crazy and an experienced rational pilot and father wouldn't have taken such a chance and risk crashing. He clearly was willing to take that chance and sadly,he lost his life and 8 others in the process. Even the local LA County Police had grounded their aircraft. If i'm a pilot with experience,i'm checking with the airports before i even begin a pre trip inspection of my aircraft. It just seems common sense and safety procedures were ignored by him. To Kobe,Giana,and the rest,may you rest in eternal peace.God Bless all of you,and your families,and friends,and to the vast public here and around the world who are mourning.
